  "description": [
    "A14 THE EVENING STAR Washington D C Monday November 17 195 t Makarios and Turks Argue Cyprus at New York Airport NEW YORK Nov 17 AP The Cyprus Issue got an airing at Idlewlld Airport yesterday as Greek Archbishop Makarios Turkish leaders from Cyprus and the Greek Foreign Minister arrived there almost simul taneously First to arrive were the Turks Then 20 minutes later the archbishop exiled leader of Greek Cypriots appeared on the scene Less than an hour later Greek Foreign Minister Evangelos AveroffTossiza landed at the airport All were coming here for the United Nations debate on the Cyprus issue and all had strong words on the subject for airport reporters Terrorism Discounted The archbishop asked about terrorism on Cyprus replied Those who give their lives for the freedom of their country are not terroriststhey are patriots Dr Fazil Kucuk leader of the Turkish community on Cyprus told reporters parti tion was the only solution be cause Turks on Cyprus want Independence as well as the Greeks Elsewhere the archbishop was telling reporters that par tition is not the solutionit is practically impossible and that if the issue of partition is kept alive conflict on the island will"
